<HEADLINE>
<P>
D-DAY ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * In response to "50 Years Later, Normandy Gets Set for 2nd Wave," May 16: 
</P>
<P>
 Your article says, " . . . Tens of thousands of World War II veterans, joined 
by President Clinton, Queen Elizabeth II and other heads of state and 
government will converge on the bluffs, the villages, the homes and the 
cemeteries of northern France on June 6 to remember D-day -- the bloody 
beginning of the end of World War II."  
</P>
<P>
 A gracious action would be for President Clinton to send as his emissary one 
of our former presidents -- Gerald Ford, Jimmy Carter or George Bush -- all war 
veterans. But such gestures are uncommon among politicians of the "me 
generation," especially, perhaps, among those who have no war record! 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN ESTERLINE 
</P>
<P>
 Claremont 
</P>
</TEXT>
