<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLAN MALAMUD: NOTES ON A SCORECARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALLAN MALAMUD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Most people give me the same answer when I ask them how they feel about the 
possibility of L.A. and Orange Counties being NFL-less by 1995. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 It goes something like this: "Oh, that's too bad, but it'll mean more games on 
TV every Sunday and that's great." . . .  
</P>
<P>
 The lack of passion for the local teams is reflected at the gate. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Al Davis' Raiders were last in the NFL in number of tickets sold for home 
games last season. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 Georgia Frontiere's Rams were 24th among the 28 teams. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders have an outdated facility, but the Cleveland Browns drew far more 
fans in a stadium that is even less attractive than the Coliseum. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 The Rams had a 5-11 record, but sold fewer tickets than the Cincinnati 
Bengals, who were 3-13. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 The Southland likes to bill itself as the sports capital of the nation. 
However, when it comes to pro football, it is the stay-away capital. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 This might not only be the best Dodger team in a number of years, but the most 
pleasant. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 "Stewardesses have told me that, as a rule, they don't enjoy working chartered 
flights involving athletic teams, but that they like this team because it is so 
well mannered," Tom Lasorda said. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 What sophomore jinx? Mike Piazza was chosen as the National League player of 
the week for May 16-22. Tim Salmon was chosen as the American League player of 
the week for May 9-15. . . . Kevin Gross' home run Monday night against the 
Chicago Cubs was the first by a Dodger pitcher this season.Too bad Darren 
Dreifort rarely gets to bat. He hit 22 home runs last year at Wichita State, 
where he also played the outfield. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Both cleanup hitters Tuesday, the Dodgers' Tim Wallach and the Cubs' Mark 
Grace, played at Saddleback College in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 Harry Caray, who is celebrating his 50th anniversary as a baseball 
broadcaster, might limit his duty to Cub home games next season. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Hall of Fame outfielder Billy Williams is listed as the Cubs' offensive 
coordinator and Chuck Cottier as their defensive coordinator. But, no, they 
don't have a quarterback coach. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Mickey Mantle hit 52 home runs in 1956, the year he set the record of 20 home 
runs in the first two months that was broken by Ken Griffey Jr. on Monday. . . 
.  
</P>
<P>
 The Colorado Rockies have never drawn fewer than 40,000 for a game at Mile 
High Stadium. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 Paul O'Neill, who is tearing up the American League and batted .311 for the 
New York Yankees last year, has a National League average of .259 in 799 
at-bats with the Cincinnati Reds. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Suspended former King Bernie Nicholls was replaced on the New Jersey Devils' 
roster by former King Corey Millen last Saturday. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Nearly 1,000 athletes, the largest number for any collegiate meet in the 
nation, will compete in the NAIA track and field championships Thursday through 
Saturday at Azusa Pacific. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Among those who have participated in the meet are Bob Hayes, Florida A & M; 
Bobby Morrow, Abilene Christian; Bruce Jenner, Graceland of Iowa; Rod Milburn, 
Southern; Billy Olson, Abilene Christian; Al Feuerbach, Emporia State, and Dave 
Johnson and Christian Okoye of Azusa Pacific, which is favored to win its 10th 
team title in 12 years. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 I wonder how Buster Mathis Jr., who fights Riddick Bowe June 11 at Caesars 
Palace, feels about the announcement that Bowe will oppose Larry Donald July 15 
at Hollywood Park. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 According to the Collegiate Licensing Company, the University of Michigan 
leads NCAA schools in nationwide sales of sports apparel and merchandise. 
Georgetown is second, Florida State third, North Carolina fourth and Alabama 
fifth. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Hakeem Olajuwon's performance in the playoffs makes his selection as NBA most 
valuable player, a regular-season award, look good. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 It is a given that the Milwaukee Bucks will draft Glenn Robinson first. The 
Dallas Mavericks, who need a point guard more than a small forward, should take 
Jason Kidd second over Grant Hill. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Reggie Miller, the Indiana Pacers' 6-foot-7 shooting guard, is supposed to 
weigh 185 pounds, but he doesn't look that heavy. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 The weekly Sprint Soccer Poll has the following top 10 three weeks before the 
start of the World Cup: Brazil, Germany, Argentina, Netherlands, Italy, 
Colombia, Belgium, a tie for eighth between Norway and Spain, and Nigeria. 
Mexico is 12th and the United States 13th. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 John McEnroe probably doesn't care about my opinion, but I think Mary Carillo 
is the best tennis commentator on TV. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 The license-plate bracket on Laffit Pincay's Porsche says: "My other car is a 
race horse." 
</P>
