<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Glick 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Palmdale 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Glick is one of the best pitchers in the area, with an 
11-2 record and 1.36 earned-run average. The hard-throwing left hander is a top 
professional prospect and has 129 strikeouts and 19 walks in 72 innings. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Glick pitched a three-hitter and struck out 17 in Palmdale's 
5-1 first-round victory over El Segundo in the Southern Section Division III 
playoffs. "He was the best we've seen this year," El Segundo Coach John 
Stevenson said. "I'm not so sure if we played him again that he wouldn't do the 
same thing." Glick loaded the bases in the first inning by hitting two batters 
and walking another. Then he struck out the next three hitters. "Our hitters 
were impressed," Stevenson said. "And I was impressed, watching them walk into 
the dugout after striking out." It was Glick's 10th complete game of the 
season. 
</P>
