THE 12TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nadia Hoerner and Valerie Miller hit back-to-back triples and Amy Simpson 
singled in Miller in the 12th inning to give Fullerton a 2-0 victory over 
fourth-seeded Lakewood in the second round of the Southern Section Division II 
softball playoffs Tuesday at Lakewood. 
</P>
<P>
 Angie Fancuberta (16-12) gave up seven hits and was supported by a solid 
defensive effort. Lakewood (22-8) had runners at second and third in the first 
inning, but had only three runners reach second base the rest of the way. In 
the fifth, left fielder Simpson threw out Amy Lewis at the plate, preventing 
the tiebreaking run. 
</P>
<P>
 Simpson and McAulay each had two hits. Fullerton (16-13) will play host to 
Covina Charter Oak Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division III softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier La Serna 1, Laguna Hills 0 (18) -- With two outs in the bottom of the 
18th, La Serna (16-7) got two hits and then a bouncer over the infield to score 
the winning run, ending Laguna Hills' hopes of defending its division title. 
Alycia Stevens and Jennifer Arzola each had three hits for Laguna Hills 
(15-10). Windy Scofield (6-5) pitched all 17 2/3 innings for the Hawks. 
</P>
<P>
 Redondo Beach Redondo Union 1, Woodbridge 0 (17 innings) -- Woodbridge 
freshman Stephanie Bernritter had a no-hitter through 12 1/3 innings, didn't 
walk a batter and struck out 10 in 16 innings before leaving with arm 
stiffness. 
</P>
<P>
 Cory Washington (10-3) replaced Bernritter and walked Selena Fine, who was 
bunted to second base. After shortstop Alison Johnsen threw out Leanna Evans at 
first base, and Fine broke for third, first baseman Keri Byrd's throw across 
the infield skidded past the third baseman and Fine scored. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnsen had three hits and a stolen base, adding to her section career record. 
She finished with 195. Winning pitcher Kari Martin struck out 16 and had the 
only hit for Redondo (20-5). Fourth-seeded Woodbridge finished 21-9. 
</P>
<P>
 South Torrance 2, Irvine 0 -- South Torrance's Rachelle Brown pitched a 
no-hitter to beat the third-seeded Vaqueros. Amy Young (17-7) struck out four 
and gave up seven hits for host Irvine (18-10). 
</P>
<P>
 In Division VI: 
</P>
<P>
 Temecula Linfield Christian 5, Liberty Christian 0 -- Linfield Christian's 
Janelle Gonzales (15-1) struck out 10 and walked one in a no-hitter. 
</P>
