<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; TOP-RANKED SIMI VALLEY BOTTOMS OUT AS GRIFFIN LOSES AT 
LOMPOC, 2-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley High, the top-ranked softball team in the state, was upset by 
Lompoc, 2-0, Tuesday in a Southern Section Division I second-round playoff game 
at Lompoc. 
</P>
<P>
 Pioneer pitcher Sara Griffin, the division's state player of the year last 
season, saw her high school career come to an end after she surrendered a 
two-run home run to Lompoc's Erin Pacheco in the fourth inning. Griffin (21-2) 
gave up two hits and struck out eight for Simi Valley (24-3). She was outdueled 
by Kim Wuest (17-1), who gave up two hits for Lompoc (21-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 2, Cerritos 0 -- Kristi Fox threw a four-hit shutout for the 
Panthers (21-7) in a Division I game at Cerritos. Fox (10-3) struck out six and 
walked one. 
</P>
<P>
 Jann Thorpe's fourth-inning double drove in Brandi Funk, and Thorpe scored on 
a throwing error. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 1, St. Joseph's 0 -- Amanda Huddleston's run-scoring double 
with two out in the ninth inning won the Division II game for the Falcons 
(22-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley's Kim Scott (12-1) pitched a three-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 5, Hart 4 -- The Cowboys (18-5-1) scored two runs in the sixth to win 
the Division II game at Hart (16-13). Each team committed eight errors. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon pitcher Kristin Mills (18-4-1) scattered eight hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus 1, Mayfair 0 -- The Centurions defeated the Monsoons in the second 
round of the Division II playoffs. Saugus will play Crescenta Valley on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Quartz Hill 5, San Dimas 2 -- Cindy Sims had two hits, including a leadoff 
home run in the first, and scored two runs for the Rebels in their Division III 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Mary Flores (10-5) scattered eight hits, struck out four and walked one for 
Quartz Hill (18-7). San Dimas dropped to 19-2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany 13, Ridgecrest Burroughs 1 -- Jamie Moore went four for four, drove in 
six runs and scored three more the Indians (22-2) in a Division III game. 
</P>
<P>
 Moore hit her third home run of the season, a three-run blast in the fourth 
inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Oak Park 11, Moorpark 5 -- Sophomore Shana Silverman went two for three and 
scored three runs for the Eagles (17-6) in the Division V game at Moorpark 
(18-6). Moorpark starting pitcher Mindy Penrod had to leave the game after 
spraining her ankle sliding into third base in the fourth inning with the 
Musketeers holding a 5-1 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 La Reina 14, Alverno 0 -- Jennifer Baltruzak tossed her second one-hitter of 
the playoffs in the Division V game at La Reina (16-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Baltruzak (11-6) recorded eight strikeouts, and also added two hits and two 
RBIs.  
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Shane Anderson slugged two home runs, including a grand slam in the 
first inning, and drove in seven runs. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Lutheran 19, Cate 11 -- Susan Riddle had three hits and six RBIs for L.A. 
Lutheran ( 14-5) in the second round Division V game. 
</P>
<P>
 Oakwood 21, West Valley Christian 1 -- Susie Vatz (16-3) tossed her second 
no-hitter this season and had 14 strikeouts in a Division VI game at Oakwood 
(16-13). BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 12, Rowland 3 -- Kirk Hagge hit a grand slam to highlight the 
Falcons' 10-run first inning in a Division I playoff game at Rowland (20-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Parque (11-2) pitched four scoreless innings, allowed one hit and struck 
out six for Crescenta Valley (18-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Gahr 7, Saugus 3 -- Saugus closed to within 4-3, but Gahr pulled away by 
scoring three runs in the sixth inning of the Division II playoff game at 
Saugus (16-9-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Brandon Hernandez (5-4) took the loss for the Centurions despite holding Gahr 
(18-7-1) to six hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 8, Tustin 5 -- Chris Tapia had two triples, scored two runs 
and drove in three for the Antelopes (14-9), who defeated defending section 
champion Tustin in the Division III playoff game. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin (22-6) tied the score, 5-5, in the fourth, but Antelope Valley 
countered with two runs in the bottom half of the inning on Tapia's two-out, 
two-run triple. 
</P>
<P>
 Coast Union 10, Oak Park 4 -- Coast Union parlayed five hits, five walks and 
three Oak Park errors into nine sixth-inning runs to eliminate the Eagles from 
the Division V playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian 3, Paraclete 1 -- Bill Kneifel had two of the Spirits' 
three hits and scored their only run in a Division V game. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus 1, Mayfair 0 -- Jamie Gillies (22-2-1) tossed a four-hitter and Kelli 
Kranz singled to drive in Jill Passafiume with the only run in a Division II 
game.  
</P>
<P>
 In City Section regular season finales: 
</P>
