<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: BERGANIO FIRES 68 TO LEAD FIELD IN U.S. OPEN QUALIFYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five area players moved a step closer to earning berths in the U.S. Open field 
during a local qualifying tournament Monday at Saticoy Country Club in 
Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany High graduate David Berganio, a two-time U.S. Public Links champion, 
took medalist honors with a four-under-par 68.Also clearing the first step of 
qualification were Rio Mesa High graduate Lawrence O'Neil (70), and 
professionals Ron Hinds of Westlake Village (71), Tom Stankowski of Ventura 
(71) and Mark Singer of Simi Valley (72). 
</P>
<P>
 Ross Fulgentis of Westlake High shot 71-76 -- 147 to finish in a tie for 21st 
place in the Ping Phoenix Junior Championships at the Karsten Golf Course at 
Arizona State last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Fulgentis finished 11 shots behind boys' champion Charley Hoffman of Poway, 
Calif., who shot a 65 in the second round. Scott Golditch of Taft finished in 
an eight-way tie for 37th at 150. Two-time City Section champion Darren Angel 
of Granada Hills struggled to a tie for 45th at 151. 
</P>
<P>
 Allison Wilson of Grant shot 82-80 -- 162 to finish 18th in the girls' 
competition. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Physical examinations for athletes in all sports will be offered at Reseda 
High from 8 a.m. till noon June 4 in the boys' gym. The cost is $15. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: Dmitri Vadetsky, Reseda assistant principal, at 883-7240, ext. 
213. 
</P>
