<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NOTES: TITANS' FERGUSON, WAGNER EARN CONFERENCE HONORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton second baseman Jeff Ferguson was named Big West Conference 
player of the year, and teammate Matt Wagner was named pitcher of the year by 
conference baseball coaches. 
</P>
<P>
 Ferguson, a junior who hit .388 with 54 runs batted in and 64 runs scored, was 
named co-player of the year with Nevada shortstop Mark Lewis. Nevada's Gary 
Powers was named conference coach of the year after leading the Wolf Pack to a 
share of the conference title with Fullerton and Long Beach State. 
</P>
<P>
 Wagner, a 6-foot-5 right-hander from Plano, Tex., finished the regular season 
12-1 with a 2.15 earned-run average. Opponents hit .212 against Wagner this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton sophomore relief pitcher Ted Silva earned first-team all-conference 
honors with Ferguson and Wagner. Titan pitcher Mike Parisi, third baseman Jason 
Gill and outfielder Mark Kotsay earned second-team honors and pitcher Dan 
Ricabal, catcher Bret Hemphill and outfielder Dante Powell were honorable 
mention selections. 
</P>
<P>
 Nevada's Neil Garcia, a catcher from Foothill High and Saddleback College, and 
Justin Drizos, a first baseman from Woodbridge High and Saddleback College, 
were named to the second team. Long Beach State pitcher Mike Fontana, formerly 
of Rancho Santiago College, earned honorable mention honors. 
</P>
<P>
 The selections: 
</P>
<P>
 First team -- Matt Wagner, So., starting pitcher, Cal State Fullerton; Scott 
Rivette, So., starting pitcher, Long Beach State; Dave Sick, Sr., starting 
pitcher, San Jose State; Ted Silva, So., relief pitcher, Cal State Fullerton; 
Victor Sanchez, Jr., catcher, Pacific; Tim Vavello, Sr., first baseman, San 
Jose State; Jeff Ferguson, Jr., second baseman, Cal State Fullerton; Curt 
Zimmerman, Jr., third baseman, Pacific; Mark Lewis, Sr., shortstop, Nevada; 
Chip Sell, Sr., outfielder, Pacific; Gus Kennedy, Jr., outfielder, Nevada Las 
Vegas; Rolando Avila, Jr., outfielder, Long Beach State; Ron Lewis, So., 
utility, Pacific; Mike Schroeder, So., designated hitter, Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
 Second team -- Mike Parisi, Jr., starting pitcher, Cal State Fullerton; Kevin 
Lake, Jr., starting pitcher, Nevada; Bobby Post, Jr., starting pitcher, Nevada; 
Gabe Gonzales, Jr., relief pitcher, Long Beach State; Neil Garcia, Jr., 
catcher, Nevada; Justin Drizos, Jr., first baseman, Nevada; Eric Martins, Sr., 
second baseman, Long Beach State; Jason Gill, Sr., third baseman, Cal State 
Fullerton; Chris Amos, Sr., shortstop, Pacific; Ryan Miller, Jr., shortstop, 
Long Beach State; Mark Kotsay, freshman, outfielder, Cal State Fullerton; Paul 
LaGreca, Jr., outfielder, New Mexico State; Jay Johnson, Jr., outfielder, 
Nevada; Shane Slayton, So., utility, Nevada; Eric Pitt, Jr., designated hitter, 
San Jose State. 
</P>
<P>
 Honorable mention -- Dan Ricabal, Sr., starting pitcher, Cal State Fullerton; 
Mike Fontana, Sr., starting pitcher, Long Beach State; Danny Miller, Sr., 
starting pitcher, Pacific; Bret Hemphill, Sr., catcher, Cal State Fullerton; 
Nick Kuster, Sr., first baseman, Nevada Las Vegas; Dante Powell, Jr., 
outfielder, Cal State Fullerton; Laverne Thomas, Sr., outfielder, San Jose 
State; Wynter Phoenix, So., outfielder, UC Santa Barbara; Ryan Plughoff, Jr., 
outfielder, Nevada Las Vegas; John Coasts, Sr., utility, Nevada Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Bailey of Long Beach Millikan has signed a letter of intent to play water 
polo at UC Irvine, Irvine Coach Ted Newland said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bailey, a 6-foot-5, 230-pound two-meter man, was a second-team All-Southern 
Section selection and is also a member of the U.S. Junior National team. 
</P>
