VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: WORKSHOP TO FOCUS ON QUAKE RECOVERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an effort to speed economic recovery from the Jan. 17 earthquake, business 
owners from Canoga Park and Reseda will attend a revitalization workshop on 
June 3 and June 4. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop, which was announced by Councilwoman Laura Chick, will address 
issues of economic revitalization, community cleanup, landscaping, crime and 
safety and historic preservation in the central business districts of Canoga 
Park and Reseda. 
</P>
<P>
 Ken Bernstein, spokesperson for Chick said the focus will primarily be 
economic. 
</P>
<P>
 Expecting a high level of participation, Tom Hillborn, president of the Reseda 
Chamber of Commerce, said, "Part of what will make this very successful is the 
timing of it. The area is in massive devastation. . . . Everyone sees the 
necessities of revitalizing the area." MAKI BECKER 
</P>
