<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; TEACHER IS STATE SCIENCE AWARD 
FINALIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A third-grade teacher at a Port Hueneme school is one of six teachers 
statewide and one of only three elementary school teachers to be named a 
finalist for the California Presidential Awards in Science. 
</P>
<P>
 Judy Burnett, who teaches at Bard School, will travel to Sacramento in June to 
receive recognition for the honor. 
</P>
<P>
 One of a team of four third-grade teachers at Bard, Burnett teaches science to 
about 120 students. She sponsors an after-school science club and takes 
students to the Navy's construction base in Port Hueneme to use high-tech 
telecommunications equipment. 
</P>
<P>
 A secret of Burnett's success in the classroom is her genuine interest and 
enthusiasm about her subject, Bard Principal Deborah DeSmeth said. 
</P>
<P>
 "She's incredibly interested in the field of science," DeSmeth said. "She has 
done a lot of background work to make sure she understands her subjects. And 
she has a love of it that shows through. She gets the kids excited about 
science." MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
