SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; PASSENGER ARRESTED IN ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK SABBATINI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Azusa man who was arrested on suspicion of robbing and assaulting another 
passenger in the bathroom of a bus as it traveled south on the Golden State 
Freeway apparently hadn't thought much about how he would make his escape. 
</P>
<P>
 Derrick Collier, 34, was arrested after he followed Vincent Schultz, 46, of 
Orange into the bathroom at the rear of the bus about 2:15 a.m. Monday, said 
Deputy Corry Cline of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department's Santa 
Clarita Valley Station. 
</P>
<P>
 Schultz told authorities that Collier punched him several times and emptied 
the contents of his pockets onto the bathroom floor before taking his money. 
Collier then returned to his seat, where he stayed until authorities arrested 
him. 
</P>
<P>
 Collier was taken into custody after Schultz reported the incident to the bus 
driver, who notified authorities and stopped near Six Flags Magic Mountain in 
Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
 Schultz was treated for minor facial injuries at Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial 
Hospital and released, authorities said. MARK SABBATINI 
