<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT TO PLACE CROSSES, FLAGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Volunteers are being sought to place more than 3,000 crosses and flags on 
veterans' graves at Loma Vista Memorial Park on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Cemetery officials are encouraging anyone who wants to help to bring 
wheelbarrows, wagons or carts to carry the crosses and flags around the 
grounds.The religious and patriotic emblems will stay on the graves until 
Memorial Day, when the U.S. Army Corp of Engineers will give a program in 
tribute to the nation's military dead. 
</P>
<P>
 The free program begins at 10 a.m. and volunteers will be needed to pick up 
the flags and crosses afterward. 
</P>
<P>
 Then, on June 1, more volunteers are being sought to iron the flags at the 
Buena Park Elks Lodge, 7212 Melrose Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 521-1867 or (714) 738-6311. MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA052594-0138 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 045060 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
May 25, 1994, Wednesday, Ventura West Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
