<P>
 North Slope Oil Production at 85% of Normal After Spill: Operations at 
Alaska's Prudhoe Bay field have been scaled back since Saturday as British 
Petroleum transferred the remaining oil from the East Lion, a tanker chartered 
by BP America Inc. that leaked 200 gallons of oil at the Port of Valdez. The 
port, the southern terminus of the Trans-Alaskan Pipeline, was closed Saturday, 
then partially reopened Monday. Production was slowed to keep the pipeline from 
carrying more oil than could be stored at Valdez. 
</P>
