<P>
 Laser Medical Technology Inc.: The San Clemente manufacturer of laser products 
and specialized biomaterials posted a net loss for the first quarter of 1994 of 
$138,000 or 2 cents a share, contrasted with a net loss of $1.6 million, or 34 
cents a share, for the first quarter of 1993. Included in the 1994 results is a 
gain of $421,000 from the ending of the company's royalties due its founder and 
former chairman, as well as a $504,000 gain on the liquidation its foreign 
subsidiary. Sales dropped to $168,000 from $478,000. 
</P>
