<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nona Morelli's II Inc.: The Irvine gaming and Italian food company reported a 
profit of $13,389, or less than a cent a share, for its third fiscal 
quarter.Included were the results of restructuring and a drop in investment 
costs. For the same period a year earlier, the company lost $898,554, or 7 
cents a share. Revenue fell 19% to $531,512 from $658,837. For the nine-month 
period, the company recorded a loss of $2.7 million, or 55 cents a share, 
contrasted with a loss of $1.9 million, or 23 cents a share, for the same 
period a year earlier. Nine-month revenue rose 18% to $2 million from $1.7 
million. 
</P>
