FLYING ROACHES DRIVING TAMPA POLICE BUGGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Tampa Police Department is fumigating 200 patrol cars to battle an 
infestation of Florida's infamous Palmetto bugs, flying roaches that eat 
everything in sight. 
</P>
<P>
 The cars are stored near a weeded area that is overrun with the voracious 
insects, which can reach two inches in length. 
</P>
